2.caption: 1956 Major League Baseball All-Star Game
2.description: The 1956 Major League Baseball All-Star Game was the 23rd playing of the midsummer classic between the all-stars of the American League (AL) and National League (NL), the two leagues comprising Major League Baseball. The game was held on July 10, 1956, at Griffith Stadium in Washington, D.C. the home of the Washington Senators of the American League.
2.inspected:Managers: Walter Alston (Brooklyn Dodgers)Casey Stengel (New York Yankees)
